AMENDED AND RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT
This AMENDED AND RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (Agreement), dated December 23, 2021 and effective as of January 1, 2022 (Effective Date), is entered into by and between Hawks Nest Hydro LLC (Hydro Owner), a limited liability company organized under the laws of the State of Delaware, and WVA Manufacturing, LLC (together with its predecessors, Smelter Owner), a limited liability company organized under the laws of the State of Delaware (each a Party, and collectively the Parties), and amends and restates in its entirety the Shared Facilities Agreement between Hydro Owner and Smelter Owners predecessor, West Virginia Alloys, Inc., dated June 6, 2006 (Original Agreement).
WITNESSETH:
WHEREAS, by deeds, assignments, bills of sale, and other instruments, each dated on or about June 13, 2006, by and between Hydro Owner and Smelter Owner. Smelter Owner conveyed to Hydro Owner certain hydroelectric assets known as Hawks Nest Hydroelectric Project (Project) located on the Kanawha and New Rivers in Fayette County, West Virginia, operated pursuant to a license issued in Project No. 2512 under Part I of the Federal Power Act issued by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC); and
WHEREAS, Hydro Owner has maintained and intends to continue to maintain Exempt Wholesale Generator or EWG status, as that term is defined by the Public Utilities Holding Company Act of 1935, 15 U.S.C. § 79a et seq., as amended, and under FERC rules governing EWGs issued in FERC Orders No. 667 and 667-A; and
WHEREAS, by deeds, assignments, bills of sale and other instruments, each dated on or about June 13, 2006, Smelter Owner conveyed to Hydro Owner certain electric delivery system facilities that connect (i) the Project to Smelter Owner's alloy plant in Fayette County, West Virginia (Manufacturing Facility) and (ii) to the transmission system of Appalachian Power Company (APC); and
WHEREAS, by deeds, assignments, bills of sale and other instruments, each dated on or about June 13, 2006, Hydro Owner conveyed to Smelter Owner an undivided ownership interest in certain electric delivery system facilities (Undivided Ownership Assets), denoted on Schedule A, which connect Hydro Owner's Project to Smelter Owner's Manufacturing Facility and to the APC system; and
WHEREAS, Smelter Owner has used and desires to continue to use the Undivided Ownership Assets to deliver energy pursuant to transactions between Smelter Owner and third parties (Smelter Owner Energy) using transmission facilities between the Manufacturing Facility and the transmission system of APC for the Manufacturing Facility; and
WHEREAS, concurrently herewith, Smelter Owner and Hydro Owners affiliate, Brookfield Energy Marketing US LLC are entering into an Amended and Restated Power Purchase Agreement (Amended and Restated PPA) setting forth the terms and conditions for sales and deliveries of energy from Hydro Owners Project to Smelter Owner;
46586523.12
WHEREAS, Hydro Owner and Smelter Owner entered into the Original Agreement to set forth their respective rights and obligations with regard to the Undivided Ownership Assets; and
WHEREAS, Hydro Owner and Smelter Owner desire to amend and restate the Original Agreement as set forth herein.
NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants and agreements set forth in this Agreement, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and adequacy of which is acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows:
AGREEMENT
1. NATURE OF OWNERSHIP INTEREST AND DEFINED TERMS
1.01 Tenancy in Common. Hydro Owner and Smelter Owner acknowledge and agree that each has an undivided ownership interest in the Undivided Ownership Assets, as tenants in common, in the proportion shown on Schedule B. Each Party acknowledges and agrees that such undivided ownership interest shall entitle each Party to the use and enjoyment of the Undivided Ownership Assets to the extent of such proportionate ownership interest, and as set forth in this Agreement.
1.02 Defined Terms. Capitalized terms used and not otherwise defined herein shall have the meanings given to such terms in the Amended and Restated PPA.
2. UNDIVIDED OWNERSHIP ASSETS
2.01 The Undivided Ownership Assets subject to this Agreement are the facilities denoted on Schedule A. Such facilities shall include generally the following: (1) an 11.6 mile, 138 kV 60 Hz transmission line connecting the APC transmission system to the switchyard adjacent to the Manufacturing Facility; (2) the 138 kV equipment in the switchyard; (3) two 60 Hz transformers located in the Manufacturing Facility switchyard; (4) portions of the 60 Hz, 13.8 kV bus and switchgear; (5) the cables between the frequency converters and the 60 Hz, 13.8 kV bus; (6) the frequency converters and associated equipment; (7) the cables from the 13.8 kV, 25 Hz bus to the frequency converters; and (8) portions of the 25 Hz, 13.2kv bus. Either Party may reasonably request Schedule A be updated to reflect any change made to the Undivided Ownership Assets, provided that any updates to Schedule A shall be in the form of a mutual written agreement of the Parties.
2.02 Allocation. As of the Effective Date of this Agreement, as defined in Article 9 herein, and at all times during the Term of this Agreement each Party's use of any Undivided Ownership Asset during any year shall be no greater than that Party's allocation of such Undivided Ownership Asset (Allocation), as defined in Schedule B. Either Party may reasonably request Schedule B be updated to reflect any change made to the Undivided Ownership Assets and the Allocations, provided that any updates to Schedule B shall be in the form of a mutual written agreement of the Parties.
2`
46586523.12
3. OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE
3.01 During the term of this Agreement, Hydro Owner shall have the exclusive right and obligation to maintain, manage and operate the Undivided Ownership Assets in accordance with the terms of this Agreement and Good Operating Practice.
(a) Good Operating Practice means any of the practices, methods and acts engaged in or approved by a significant portion of the electricity generating industry in the United States of America during the relevant time period that operate facilities similar to the Project and practices, methods, and acts, which in the exercise of reasonable judgment in light of the facts known at the time the decision was made, could have been expected to accomplish the desired result at a reasonable cost consistent with Law, good business practices, reliability, safety and expedition. Good Operating Practice is not intended to be limited to the optimum practice, method or act to the exclusion of all others, but rather includes all acceptable practices, methods, or acts generally accepted by the United States electricity generating industry that operate facilities similar to the Project.
(b) Hydro Owner shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to schedule maintenance outages (including the timing, duration, and scope of such outages) with Smelter Owner to minimize disruption to the Manufacturing Facility. Hydro Owner shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to provide Smelter Owner with advance notice of all planned maintenance outages at least thirty (30) days in advance and will use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to accommodate timely and reasonable requests from Smelter Owner to reschedule or modify such outages; provided, however, that in the event that Hydro Owner is unable to provide thirty (30) days advance notice to Smelter Owner of a maintenance outage, Hydro Owner shall have the right to schedule maintenance outages with shorter notice or without notice to Smelter Owner to the extent necessary to ensure the Undivided Ownership Assets are operated and maintained in accordance with Good Operating Practice; provided that Hydro Owner shall notify Smelter Owner, as soon as reasonably practicable of such maintenance outages and shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to minimize disruption to the Manufacturing Facility.
3.02 Description of Work. Hydro Owner, at its own cost and expense, but subject to reimbursement of any costs and expenses for any Work (as defined below) that meets the definition of Operating Expenses under Section 7.01, shall provide or arrange for all services, personnel and labor necessary to perform the Work, which is defined as follows:
(a) providing or arranging for the assignment and availability of sufficient numbers of qualified and trained personnel, tools, and equipment for on-site operation and maintenance of the Undivided Ownership Assets in compliance with applicable laws and consistent with Good Operating Practice;
(b) performing, or causing to be performed, all day-to-day operation of the Undivided Ownership Assets;
3`
46586523.12
(c) delivering or causing to be delivered all Smelter Owner Energy between the APC transmission system and the Manufacturing Facility on 24 hours per day, 365 days per year basis, without interruption, except as otherwise contemplated by this Agreement;
(d) monitoring each Party's use of the Undivided Ownership Assets to ensure that no Party uses the Undivided Ownership Assets in excess of its Allocation;
(e) performing designated and requested repair and maintenance in accordance with Good Operating Practice (including promptly repairing in accordance with the manufacturer's directions and in good and workmanlike manner any equipment that fails or malfunctions or performs at a level or in a manner inconsistent with the manufacturer's specifications and performance standards);
(f) providing qualified and trained personnel for testing and recalibrating, in accordance with Good Operating Practice and applicable laws, any scales, meters, gauges or other measuring devices associated with the Undivided Ownership Assets;
(g) keeping all real property and all personal property and equipment associated with or part of the Undivided Ownership Assets free and clear of all liens and encumbrances caused by any action or failure to act by Hydro Owner in the performance of its obligations under this Agreement, including, without limitation, failure by Hydro Owner to pay, when due, any bill or charge for labor or services performed or materials or equipment furnished for use in connection with this Agreement, except to the extent such liens are caused by Smelter Owner or are attributable to Smelter Owner's failure to make payments when due. Nothing herein contained shall require Hydro Owner to pay any claims for labor, materials or services which Hydro Owner, in good faith, disputes and which Hydro Owner, at its own expense, is currently and diligently contesting in good faith; provided, however, that (i) none of the Undivided Ownership Assets, any associated rights of way, easements, licenses, permits or other interests in real or personal property, nor any part thereof, are or will be in danger of being forfeited, terminated, cancelled or lost and that Hydro Owner shall pay the amount of any such claims, together with any costs, interest and/or penalties that may be payable in connection therewith or otherwise post a bond or take other action to remove such threat of termination, forfeiture, loss or cancellation promptly upon determination of same, and (ii) Hydro Owner shall, not later than thirty (30) days (or such shorter period to the extent necessary to prevent any of the Undivided Ownership Assets, any associated rights of way, easements, licenses, permits or other interests in real or personal property, or any part thereof, from becoming in danger of being forfeited, terminated, cancelled or lost) after notice of the filing of any claim of lien that is disputed or contested by Hydro Owner, post a surety bond sufficient to release said claim of lien;
(h) delivering to Smelter Owner within twenty (20) days of Smelter Owner's written request, up to four (4) times each calendar year, a report of activities, including a summary of repair and maintenance activities performed on the Undivided Ownership Assets during the prior period and the costs thereof;
4`
46586523.12
(i) paying all personal property and real estate taxes when due on the Undivided Ownership Assets;
(j) performing tests to monitor the safety and performance of the Undivided Ownership Assets in accordance with Good Operating Practice and applicable laws;
(k) maintaining adequate insurance coverage, as mutually agreed by the Parties, on the Undivided Ownership Assets;
(l) subject to Section 3.02(m), upgrading the Frequency Converter Facilities, including installing related equipment;
(m) ensuring that the Frequency Converter Facilities, including upon completion of any Unit Upgrade, retain the capacity to convert at least 48 MW from 60 Hz to 25 Hz and at least 48 MW from 25 Hz to 60 Hz; and
(n) using Commercially Reasonable Efforts, including, if commercially reasonable, installing any additional equipment that may be necessary for purposes of this Section 3.02(n), to maintain the reliability of delivery of 25 Hz energy (including 60 Hz energy converted to 25 Hz energy as applicable) to the Delivery Point.
3.03 Services Agreement. Hydro Owner may subcontract its management and maintenance services hereunder to one or more other persons or entities, including, without limitation, Smelter Owner.
3.04 Payment of Fines, Penalties and Liquidated Damages. If at any time commencing on the Effective Date and continuing for the remainder of the term of this Agreement, any fine or penalty becomes payable as a result of the failure of the Undivided Ownership Assets to meet any environmental law, regulation, order or permit promulgated thereunder, such fine or penalty shall be borne equally by the Hydro Owner and Smelter Owner; provided, however, that Hydro Owner shall be solely responsible for fines or penalties that are the result of the negligence, willful misconduct, or the failure to follow Good Operating Practice or applicable laws on the part of Hydro Owner after the date hereof.
3.05 Limitations. (a) Hydro Owner may not, without the prior written consent of Smelter Owner, which shall not be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed, unless otherwise required by a Government Agency or a requirement of any FERC License:
(i) make any expenditures for materials, equipment, services, or supplies for Undivided Ownership Assets in excess of $25,000;
(ii) enter into any contracts on behalf of Smelter Owner or take any other actions in the name of or on behalf of Smelter Owner except as otherwise specifically authorized under this Agreement;
5`
46586523.12
(iii) take any action in respect of the Undivided Ownership Assets other than as set forth in this Agreement or otherwise in the ordinary course of performing the obligations of Smelter Owner;
(iv) cause the conveyance, material modification, sale or other disposition of any part of the Undivided Ownership Assets except pursuant to the terms of this Agreement; or
(v) generate or otherwise bring onto the Manufacturing Facility any chemical, material or hazardous substance that is regulated by applicable laws, except in accordance with Smelter Owner's guidelines regarding the handling, use, and disposal of such materials to the extent such guidelines are reasonably necessary to comply with applicable laws.
(b) Hydro Owner shall submit its request for the prior written consent of Smelter Owner required by Section 3.05(a) to Smelter Owner in writing, detailing the action proposed. In the event that Hydro Owner does not receive Smelter Owners written response within thirty (30) days of the request therefor, Smelter Owner shall be deemed to have consented in writing to the action proposed in such request. Should Smelter Owner reject Hydro Owners request for prior written consent, the Parties shall submit such dispute resolution pursuant to Article 8.
(c) Notwithstanding the foregoing, Hydro Owner may, without the prior written consent of Smelter Owner: make expenditures; install, replace, repair, convert and upgrade equipment; and take all other actions with respect to the Undivided Ownership Assets that are reasonably required in accordance with Good Operating Practice, if (x) such actions could not reasonably be expected to result in a material adverse effect on Smelter Owner or the Manufacturing Facility, (y) such actions are not prohibited under Sections 3.05(a)(ii) through (v), and (z) the costs of such actions will be borne solely by Hydro Owner or will not exceed the limit in Section 3.05(a)(i). In connection with any modifications, upgrades, conversions or additions to any of the Undivided Ownership Assets, Hydro Owner shall provide to Smelter Owner in writing detailed plans for such modifications and upgrades at least thirty (30) days in advance of commencing work on any such actions. If Smelter Owner provides Hydro Owner with any written comments on such plans within fifteen (15) days after receipt of such Plans, then Hydro Owner shall make Commercially Reasonable Efforts to accommodate such comments before commencing such work. Any dispute between the Parties in connection with this Section 3.05(c) shall be submitted for dispute resolution pursuant to Article 8.
3.06 Smelter Owner Right of Access. Except as set forth in this Section 3.06 or as set forth in the Operating Procedures, but subject to the rights the Smelter Owner has as owner of the real property on which any of the Undivided Ownership Assets are located, including the right to access facilities and equipment solely owned and operated by Smelter Owner for the sole purpose of operating and maintaining such equipment, Smelter Owner shall not have the right of access to the Undivided Ownership Assets without the prior approval of Hydro Owner, which shall not be unreasonably withheld or delayed. Smelter Owner shall comply with Hydro Owner's safety protocols during any access.
6`
46586523.12
(a) In the event of an imminent danger to life or the Smelter Owners property requiring immediate access to the Undivided Ownership Assets by APC or its successor network services provider (Transmission Provider) to protect life or Smelter Owners property, to mitigate such imminent danger to life or to Smelter Owners property, no such prior approval shall be required for the limited purpose of remediating such imminent danger; provided, however, Smelter Owner shall provide Hydro Owner with specific notice immediately or as soon as practicable, of each of (i) the existence of such imminent danger, (ii) Smelter Owners remedial efforts and (iii) the cessation of such imminent danger. Smelter Owners rights under this Section 3.06(a) shall be exercised only in the event that Hydro Owners representatives, employees, contractors or agents are not on-site diligently remediating the imminent danger. Smelter Owner shall cease its remedial efforts immediately upon the assumption of diligent remedial actions by Hydro Owner, its employees, contractors or agents.
(b) In the exercise of its rights pursuant to this Section 3.06, Smelter Owner will use all Commercially Reasonable Efforts to avoid interference with Hydro Owners uninterrupted operation, undue damage to the Undivided Ownership Assets or danger to life or property. Smelter Owner shall be liable to and shall hold harmless and indemnify Hydro Owner for any Losses as defined in Section 11.01 herein incurred by Hydro Owner in connection with Smelter Owners exercise of its right to self-help under this Section 3.06.
(c) Hydro Owner and Smelter Owner shall cooperate in (i) identifying the risks that would likely cause Smelter Owner to exercise its rights to self-help and (ii) developing common safety standards and emergency protocols to assist Smelter Owner in exercising its rights to self-help, which shall be set forth in the Operating Procedures.
3.07 Hydro Owner Right of Access. Subject to this Section 3.07 and the Operating Procedures, Smelter Owner hereby grants to Hydro Owner and its contractors, subcontracts and suppliers, reasonable access to the land owned by Smelter Owner to timely and efficiently install switchgear as set forth on Schedule D and approved by Smelter Owner (not to be unreasonably withheld, delayed or conditioned), which access shall be to permit Hydro Owner to progress with such equipment on a continuous basis without substantial interruption or interference. In the exercise of its rights pursuant to this Section 3.07, Hydro Owner will use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to avoid interference with Smelter Owners uninterrupted operation, undue damage to the Smelter Assets or danger to life or property. Except to the extent prior notice is not feasible due to imminent danger to any persons or physical property, Hydro Owner shall provide Smelter Owner with at least twenty four (24) hours advance, written notice before exercising the access rights under this Section 3.07. Hydro Owner shall be liable to and shall hold harmless and indemnify Smelter Owner for any Losses as defined in Section 11.01 herein incurred by Smelter Owner in connection with Hydro Owners exercise of its rights under this Section 3.07.
3.08 Operating Procedures. Smelter Owner and Hydro Owner shall cooperate in good faith to develop, as soon as reasonably practicable, written operating procedures (Operating Procedures) regarding provision of the Work and exercise of other rights and obligations in 7`
46586523.12
accordance with this Agreement, including detailed requirements for staffing, training, timing of actions, communications, access to real property, safety, and other procedural matters. The Parties shall reasonably consider any changes to the Operating Procedures proposed by either Party. The Parties shall mutually agree in writing to the Operating Procedures or any changes to them.
4. MUTUAL COVENANTS
4.01 Each Party shall define its delivery points for any internal or external sales or purchases, to be included in the schematic diagram attached to Schedule A to this Agreement, and as may be amended from time to time.
4.02 The Parties shall use all Commercially Reasonable Efforts to ensure that their respective electrical systems are equipped with adequate protective devices and protection schemes, which are tested periodically to ensure their good working order, all in accordance with applicable standards and good engineering practice, to correct or clear faults and abnormal conditions. The parties shall coordinate their protective systems so that that faults and abnormal conditions shall be cleared in such a manner as to avoid unnecessary disconnection of loads or generation, and so that protective devices operate in the correct sequence.
4.03 The Parties shall keep each other provided with current information on their electrical systems and the Undivided Ownership Assets, including system characteristics, fault data, relay settings, drawings, and metering and process data for the Undivided Ownership Assets.
4.04 Each Party shall communicate to the other Party, in advance and in writing, plans for significant changes to its respective electrical systems, in order to facilitate budgeting and work planning.
4.05 The Parties shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to keep each other informed, and to provide as much advance notice as possible to the other, of any matters which may affect or disrupt the other's business, facilities, or operations and shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to minimize such effects or disruptions.
4.06 Hydro Owner and Smelter Owner agree that each of the owners of the Undivided Ownership Assets may use the Allocation owned by it only for its own exclusive use, benefit and profit, and that of its Affiliates, in each case only to the extent of each Party's Allocation and otherwise subject to the terms of this Agreement.
4.07 Hydro Owner and Smelter Owner agree that the Undivided Ownership Assets of Hydro Owner and Smelter Owner shall be separate from and not merge with or otherwise relate to the fee ownership of the land on or over which the Undivided Ownership Assets are located.
4.08 No Compensation or Public Use. Hydro Owner and Smelter Owner agree that use of the Undivided Ownership Assets is not provided for compensation. Unless specifically ordered by a governmental authority having jurisdiction over the use of the Undivided Ownership Assets, neither Hydro Owner nor Smelter Owner shall provide access by the public to any of the Undivided Ownership Assets. 8`
46586523.12
4.09 Acts Required by FERC; Compliance with Laws. Notwithstanding any provision contained in this Agreement, Hydro Owner shall have the right to perform any and all acts (each an Act) required by any Federal, state or local governmental authority having authority over the Project, including, but not limited to an order of FERC affecting the Project, without the prior approval of Smelter Owner or any other person. In the performance of any such Act, Hydro Owner shall provide Smelter Owner with as much prior written notice as practicable. In the performance of any such Act, Hydro Owner shall use its best efforts to minimize any interference with the operation of the Manufacturing Facility.
4.10 The Parties agree that, in the event either Party desires to seek separate interconnection agreements and arrangements, the non-requesting Party will engage in Commercially Reasonable Efforts to assist and support the requesting Party and will otherwise not impede the efforts of the requesting Party.
4.11 Each Party agrees that it shall reasonably cooperate to provide to the other Party the services of its employees, on a cost-reimbursable basis to the extent that such employees have skills and experience that are reasonably required by the other Party and are available to perform services for the other Party.
5. SMELTER OWNER COVENANTS
5.01 Smelter Owner covenants and agrees that, during the term of this Agreement, its use of the Undivided Ownership Assets will be only for the purposes of power delivery, protecting all parties' systems by regulating power flow and synchronizing the power output of the Project with the Transmission Provider's transmission system, and other actions consistent with maintaining Hydro Owner's EWG status.
5.02 Smelter Owner covenants and agrees that, during the term of this Agreement, it shall not take any action (or fail to take any action) in respect of the Undivided Ownership Assets that would cause Hydro Owner to lose its EWG status under applicable law or FERC regulations, except as expressly required by applicable laws or as authorized by Hydro Owner. Smelter Owner covenants and agrees that, during the existence of this Agreement, it shall comply with all terms and provisions of any rights of way, easements, licenses, permits or other interests in real property associated with and/or comprising any of the Undivided Ownership Assets and shall not take any action or fail to take any action that is reasonably likely to result in the termination, cancellation or forfeiture of any such rights or way, easements, licenses, permits or other interests in real property associated with and/or comprising any of the Undivided Ownership Assets.
5.03 Smelter Owner covenants and agrees that, during the term of this Agreement and except as associated with financing as allowed under Section 18.01, it shall keep the Undivided Ownership Assets free and clear of all liens and encumbrances.
5.04 Smelter Owner shall provide a continuous supply of low-voltage AC power and DC power for the operation and maintenance of the Hydro Owners 69 kV substation adjacent to the Manufacturing Facility, of characteristics and quantity sufficient for the proper operation of the equipment, consistent with past practice. 9`
46586523.12
6. HYDRO OWNER'S COVENANTS
6.01 Hydro Owner covenants and agrees that, during the existence of this Agreement, its use of the Undivided Ownership Assets will be only for the purposes of power delivery, protecting all parties' systems by regulating power flow, synchronizing the power output of the Project with the Transmission Provider's transmission system, and other actions consistent with maintaining its EWG status.
6.02 Hydro Owner covenants and agrees that, during the term of this Agreement, it shall not take any action (or fail to take any action) in respect of the Undivided Ownership Assets that would cause Smelter Owner to be regulated as a public utility under the Federal Power Act, except as expressly required by applicable laws or authorized by Smelter Owner. Hydro Owner covenants and agrees that, during the existence of this Agreement, it shall comply will all terms and provisions of any rights of way, easements, licenses, permits or other interests in real property associated with and/or comprising any of the Undivided Ownership Assets and shall not take any action or fail to take any action that is reasonably likely to result in the termination, cancellation or forfeiture of any such rights or way, easements, licenses, permits or other interests in real property associated with and/or comprising any of the Undivided Ownership Assets.
6.03 Hydro Owner shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to operate and maintain, or cause the operation and maintenance of, the Project in accordance with Good Operating Practice, applicable Law and Governmental Approvals and otherwise in accordance with this Agreement.
7. PAYMENTS
7.01 Allocated Operating Expenses.
(a) Hydro Owner and Smelter Owner agree to share in the expense of operation, maintenance and repair of the Undivided Ownership Assets, and agree that Hydro Owner is to be paid no compensation, profit or return on investment in any way under this Agreement. Commencing one month after the Effective Date, and through the expiration or termination of this Agreement, Smelter Owner shall pay to Hydro Owner Smelter Owner's pro rata share of the Operating Expenses (as defined below) for the Undivided Ownership Assets based upon the Parties' Allocations (or as otherwise agreed in writing between the Parties in accordance with Section 7.01(b)).
(b) Operating Expenses for purposes of this Agreement, shall be defined to include Hydro Owner's reasonable out-of-pocket payments to third parties for Work performed in accordance with Article 3 (excluding work performed pursuant to Section 3.05(c)), including the operation, maintenance and repair of the Undivided Ownership Assets and the upgrade of the Frequency Converter Facilities as set forth in Schedule C, its pro rata labor expenses for its employees performing operation, services, insurance, taxes, and other costs reasonably incurred in servicing, operating, maintaining and repairing the Undivided Ownership Assets and upgrading the Frequency Converter Facilities as set forth in Schedule C. Any dispute between the Parties in connection with this Section 7.01(b) shall be submitted for dispute resolution pursuant to Article 8. 10`
46586523.12
7.02 Invoicing. Within twenty (20) calendar days after the conclusion of each month during the term of this Agreement, Hydro Owner shall send Smelter Owner an itemized list of the Operating Expenses incurred by Hydro Owner during the prior month together with all supporting invoices and such other documentation that may be reasonably requested by Hydro Owner to support the amount of the Operating Expenses.
7.03 Payment of Operating Expenses. Hydro Owner shall invoice Smelter Owner for Smelter Owners share of the Operating Expenses provided hereunder on a monthly basis and shall provide reasonable documentation supporting the amounts owed pursuant to Section 7.02 hereof. Smelter Owner shall pay the amount of such invoice by electronic transfer of immediately available funds to any bank account designated in writing by Hydro Owner, not later than thirty (30) days after receipt of an invoice. In the event Smelter Owner does not timely pay Hydro Owner (i) all amounts so payable and past due shall accrue interest from the 30th day after the receipt of the invoice to the receipt of payment at a floating rate per annum equal to the per annum interest rate published in the "Money Rates" section of the Wall Street Journal (or if such rate is no longer published by the Wall Street Journal, over the prime rate for large United States money center commercial banks as published by mutually-acceptable national financial publication) as the prime rate in effect, plus two percent (2%), and (ii) Smelter Owner shall pay, as additional fees, all reasonable costs and expenses incurred by Hydro Owner in attempting to collect and collecting amounts due under this Article 7, including all reasonable attorneys' fees and expenses.
8. DISPUTE RESOLUTION
8.01 Senior Officers. (a) In the event any dispute arises under this Agreement, such dispute shall be referred by each Party to a senior officer designated by Seller and a senior officer designated by Buyer for resolution upon five (5) Business Days' written notice from either Party. Any dispute that may arise in connection with this Agreement which cannot be resolved within thirty (30) Days following submission to senior officers shall be settled by arbitration in accordance with Section 8.02, as applicable.
(b) The Parties hereto agree (i) to attempt to resolve all disputes arising hereunder promptly, equitably and in a good faith manner; and (ii) to provide each other with reasonable access during normal business hours to any and all non-privileged records, information and data pertaining to any such dispute.
8.02 Arbitration. (a) After the expiration of the thirty (30) Day period described in Section 8.01(a), either Party may submit any matter in dispute concerning the provisions of this Agreement to arbitration by providing the other Party a written notice of arbitration, specifying the matter to be arbitrated.
(b) Within twenty (20) Days of the notice given in Section 8.02 (a), the Parties shall select an AAA approved commercial arbitrator, unless the Parties otherwise agree in writing to select the arbitrator from another source. To select the arbitrator, the Parties shall alternately strike names from a list obtained from the AAA or other agreed upon source of fifteen (15) commercial arbitrators knowledgeable or experienced in the industry with no financial interest in
11`
46586523.12
any Party or any Affiliate of any Party, with the Party furnishing the Notice of Arbitration striking first, until one Person's name remains on such list. Such Person shall become the arbitrator of the matter. In the event the Person selected to be an arbitrator is unable or unwilling to serve, the process shall be repeated until one arbitrator has been selected and has agreed to hear and resolve the dispute.
(c) The arbitrator shall permit each Party to conduct reasonable discovery as promptly and expeditiously as possible (and both Parties shall cooperate to this end). Discovery shall be limited to requests for the production of documents and examination upon deposition. Each Party's requests for, and responses to, discovery including examination upon deposition shall be completed within sixty (60) Days of the arbitrators' selection. The Parties may modify the period for discovery by mutual agreement. The arbitrator shall resolve any discovery disputes between the Parties that, after using reasonable efforts, the Parties cannot resolve themselves.
(d) The hearing shall be initiated as promptly and expeditiously as possible (and the Parties shall cooperate to this end) and, in no event more than thirty (30) Days after the conclusion of the discovery period. The rules of evidence of AAA shall apply to the presentation of evidence. Each Party shall file written direct testimony with the arbitrator and serve a copy on the other Party. The written testimony must be received by the arbitrator and the other Party no later than ten (10) Days prior to the commencement of the hearing. Each Party shall be permitted to make opening statements with the Party demanding arbitration presenting its opening statement first. Immediately after opening statements, the Party demanding arbitration shall then present evidence in support of its position. The other Party then shall present evidence in support of its position. All witnesses must testify under oath, and a stenographic record and transcript of the hearing shall be made. Each Party shall have an opportunity to cross-examine the other Party's witnesses, including the witnesses that file written direct testimony. The Parties shall be permitted to make closing statements. The Party demanding arbitration shall present its statement first. The arbitrator shall conclude the hearing within thirty (30) calendar days of its commencement. The period for concluding the hearing may be modified by mutual agreement of the Parties.
(e) The Parties shall submit briefs and/or proposed orders following the completion of the hearing unless otherwise agreed by the Parties and approved by the arbitrator. Initial briefs or proposed orders shall be served on other Parties. The initial briefs or proposed orders must be received by the arbitrator and the other Party no later than fifteen (15) Days after completion of the hearing. Reply briefs shall be submitted to the arbitrator and served on the other Party within ten (10) Days of receipt by the arbitrator and the other Party of the initial briefs or proposed orders. The briefing schedule provided herein may be modified by mutual agreement of the Parties with the approval of the arbitrator.
(f) The determination and/or award of the arbitrator, whichever is appropriate, shall be made no later than thirty (30) Days from the date of the completion of the hearing or, if applicable, the date the last required briefs and/or proposed orders were received by the arbitrator and the Parties.
